translate ru ArrivingInLethram_a20c35fd:
    # "Sarah and Kate walk through the harbor district of Lethram."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_f9d638b0:
    # "Sarah is in awe of the sights. She imagined the capital of Rosanna to have a large port, but by comparison to Lethram, it was a backwater."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_e42df022:
    # "Everywhere she looks, she sees swarms of people, going about all manner of business. Crates, being loaded and offloaded from ships. Market stalls, selling fruits she had never seen in her life before."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_6cc2c519:
    # "Sarah began to realize how growing up in a castle had left her closed off from the real world."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_41d92f4b:
    # "The city state of Lethram is situated on a peninsula, bordered by several great powers. Across the sea, the city connects to many more places."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_436496d8:
    # "The city's central positioning made it a hub for trading in the region."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_32e22b69:
    # "Lethram's city council has, when the occasion called for it, used their large coffers to hire mercenary bands, to guarantee their independence."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_d447ad04:
    # "Following rising tensions with its western neighbour Mythran, Lethram has extended a contract to the \"Brothers of Providence\", the mercenary band that Kate works for."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_758d486d:
    # "Kate grabbed Sarah's hand."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_cdd25516:
    # k "Don't let go, Lethram is a big city, and you don't want to end up lost."
    k ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_64569bbf:
    # "With ease, Kate guided Sarah through the masses of people, ducking and weaving."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_bb3be2cf:
    # "By contrast, Sarah found herself bumping into people, apologizing left and right. Crowds like these were new to here."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_0e2bf498:
    # "But Kate never let go of her hand."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_e1c4f218:
    # "Not long after, they left the harbor district and began walking on a road leading up into the city's shop district."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_c50fa049:
    # "The crowds grew thinner, but it still seemed like a lot of people to Sarah."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_7aae8fa2:
    # s "How much farther is it?"
    s ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_70270969:
    # k "It's not much further. The camp is set up in one of the old marketplaces."
    k ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_46714cba:
    # "Kate kept her stride and spoke without looking back."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_8e5a665f:
    # k "It's just up this road and off to the left."
    k ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_98634069:
    # "Sarah looked into the shops of the windows she passed by, being hurried along by Kate."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_48339cec:
    # "She wondered if Kate might want to go visit some with her, later."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_af0a87c4:
    # "She was in danger, Kate had warned her as much, but right now, Sarah found herself too distracted to worry."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_c92f7750:
    # "That a world like this could have been out here..."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_c942a928:
    # "Just as Kate had said, not long after, they made it to the entrance of the mercenary camp."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_74acb004:
    # k "We're here."
    k ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_d6208ace:
    # "The mercenary camp, belonging to the Brothers of Providence, was different from what Sarah had expected."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_391884b4:
    # "Situated in the middle of an old marketplace, the camp was surrounded by tall houses, making it feel walled in."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_0b359469:
    # "The alleyways leading in and out of the camp, had been either boarded up or turned into watchposts."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_fb7ed2a9:
    # "Kate exchanged a quick nod with the guard at the entrance, and he allowed her and Sarah to pass through."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_5d64937f:
    # "Inside the camp the feeling of claustrophobia only grew."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_05bc79fa:
    # "The narrow alleys were stacked with crates, leaving little space to move."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_73bb03de:
    # "Overhead, large sheets had been pulled across to block the sun. It made Sarah feel like she had entered a cave."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_9de7234c:
    # "All around them, soldiers were moving and bustling in various directions, engaged in various tasks."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_c473ab29:
    # "With her dress, Sarah stood out, but only drew some casual glances."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_3f81bd5b:
    # "Sarah was used to the army back in Rosanna, every soldier, wearing the exact same uniform. This mercenary company was the opposite. She saw no two soldiers that looked alike."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_a3560171:
    # "There were men, women, working side by side, and Sarah even saw some other species."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_9c1def64:
    # "Except for the occasional merchant, Rosanna was almost exclusively a human kingdom. Books were Sarah's only source on non-human species."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_be64c9a3:
    # "One species, she instantly recognized."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_daa316e1:
    # "A great brute of an orc sat outside the entrance to a tent, sliding a whetstone across a two-handed sword, sharpening it. The sword alone, Sarah thought, was bigger than herself."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_16f504b9:
    # "The orc was easily a head taller than any man in the camp. The lines on his face seemed to suggest he was old, but his upper body had more muscles than Sarah had ever seen on any man."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_c2d86a49:
    # "And an equal number of scars, she realized."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_93713817:
    # "Sarah looked up from the orc's body, only to find the orc staring back at her."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_cc3c7a51:
    # "Green eyes, filled with anger. Not so much directed at her, as at everyone in general."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_bb7126a0:
    # "Frightened, Sarah quickly turned her head away and continued to follow in Kate's footsteps."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_c1c4ce12:
    # "Kate comforted her."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_9b1480c3:
    # k "Don't worry. Keep to yourself and everyone will treat you just fine."
    k ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_52a43463:
    # "Finally, Kate led Sarah to a small tent, towards the center of the camp."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_2c9de62e:
    # "All around the area, there were similar small tents, each housing a few soldiers."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_964ad9e7:
    # "Kate pulled Sarah into the tent and closed the flap."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_e833f108:
    # "Though Sarah could still hear the sounds of the camp around her, there was some degree of privacy here."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_47597fe5:
    # "Kate sat down and pulled Sarah next to her, on a small cot."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_8d2e3fc4:
    # k "We made it..."
    k ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_7fb2aa90:
    # "Kate seemed to finally relax, letting go of everything she had been holding onto. Her shoulders sagging a bit."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_17007ce7:
    # "Sarah looked at Kate."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_c1bb8eb1:
    # s "This is where I'll be safe?"
    s ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_8ab0a8a4:
    # "It was a tiny tent, on the other side of the world, in a camp full of strangers..."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_539b544c:
    # "Kate nodded."
    ""

translate ru ArrivingInLethram_fa53427a:
    # k "I know it looks like...well...what it looks like, but trust me, these people will keep you safe...just like they kept me safe when they found me all those years ago."
    k ""

